        "calculation": "1. Calculate the angular difference between Moon's longitude and Sun's longitude (Moon_longitude - Sun_longitude). Ensure the result is between 0 and 360 degrees by adding 360 if negative. 2. If this difference is greater than 180 degrees (6 signs), subtract it from 360 degrees (12 signs) to obtain the smaller arc. 3. Convert this final arc into degrees. 4. Divide the result by 3. This value is the Paksha Bala for benefic planets.",
