        "condition": "When evaluating the strength and impact of planetary relationships (Sambandha) between two or more planets as described in classical texts.",
        "calculation": "Identify the type of relationship(s) present between planets. The text explicitly states 'पूर्वपूर्वाः स्युः सम्बन्धा बलवत्तराः' (the preceding relationships are stronger). Therefore, the relationships are to be ordered by strength as they appear in the text: 1. Vyatyastashraya (Mutual Exchange of signs/Parivartana Yoga), 2. Anyaloka Sambhavah (Mutual Aspect), 3. Ekasya Rashau Samsthitya Tadishaloka Nadapi (One planet in the sign of another, and aspected by its lord), 4. Sahavasashtha (Co-existence/Association, often interpreted as conjunction or being in Kendra/Trikona). The first mentioned is the strongest, and the strength decreases sequentially.",
        "threshold": null,
        "comparison": null
      },
      "halt_on_failure": false,
      "impact_if_violated": "Incorrect assessment of the relative strength and influence of planetary relationships, leading to erroneous interpretation of yogas and planetary effects on various life aspects and predictions.",
