        "calculation": "1. Identify the Ascendant Lord (Lagnesha) in the Rashi chart. 2. Identify the Navamsha Lord of the Ascendant (Lagna Bhagesha) in the Rashi chart (i.e., the lord of the sign where the Lagna falls in the Navamsha chart). 3. For the Lagnesha:    a. Check if its Rashi chart placement is in the 6th, 8th, or 12th house from the Ascendant.    b. Check if it is in conjunction with any Markesh planet.    c. Check if it is aspected by any Markesh planet. 4. For the Lagna Bhagesha:    a. Check if its Rashi chart placement is in the 6th, 8th, or 12th house from the Ascendant.    b. Check if it is in conjunction with any Markesh planet.    c. Check if it is aspected by any Markesh planet. 5. The yoga is present if ALL conditions (3a OR 3b OR 3c) AND (4a OR 4b OR 4c) are met for BOTH lords.",
